{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Preheat oven to 160°C.","Place water into mixing bowl. Place Varoma into position and weigh apples into it. Secure Varoma lid and steam <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>.","Stir apples with spatula to ensure even cooking, then steam for a further <b>10 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b> or until apples are tender.","Transfer apples into a deep-sided oval ovenproof dish (23 x 16 x 6 cm) and set aside. Discard steaming water and dry mixing bowl.","Place dates into mixing bowl and chop <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Add oil, sugar, vanilla and egg and mix <b>10 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour, cinnamon and buttermilk and mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then mix <b>5 sec\/speed 5<b>.","Spoon mixture over apples to cover, lightly spray with olive oil and bake for 25-35 minutes (160°C), or until topping is lightly golden and cooked. Sprinkle with extra cinnamon and serve with yoghurt (optional)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["600 g water","5 Granny Smith apples (approx. 700 g), peeled, cored and cut into dice","60 g pitted dates","60 g extra virgin olive oil","2 tbsp brown sugar (see Tips)","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","1 egg","160 g wholemeal self-raising flour","½ tsp ground cinnamon, plus extra to serve","160 g buttermilk","olive oil spray","plain yoghurt, to serve (optional)"]}],"id":"r122264","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-MkmmduVPB64\/XZWdNPEtZCI\/AAAAAAAAejE\/x8Bq1163FAc8kHHyD_CmhCAMC6YrTc6yACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_CgQtBY0Z2u5M_18v.png","title":"Apple sponge pudding","publishedAt":"2017-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6.1 g","fat":"14.1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"44.1 g","calories":"1417 kJ \/ 337 kcal"},"usefulItems":"ovenproof baking dish, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can use your preferred brown sugar in this recipe – either regular brown sugar or a less refined option such as Rapadura sugar (Panela) or coconut sugar.","If you prefer, you can serve this pudding with custard instead of yoghurt, such as the Better-for-you custard on this recipe chip."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","1h 20m","6 portions"]}